{"review": [{"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 0, "sentence": "The paper is well written and easy to follow. The topic is apt."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 1, "sentence": "I don\u2019t have any comments except the following ones."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Lemma 2.4, Point 1: The proof is confusing."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 3, "sentence": "Consider the one variable vector case."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 4, "sentence": "Assuming that there is only one variable w, then \\nabla L(w) is not perpendicular to w in general."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 5, "sentence": "The Rayleigh quotient example L(w)  = w\u2019*A*w/ (w\u2019*w) for a symmetric matrix A, then \\nabla L(w) = (2/w\u2019*w)(Aw - L(w)*w), which is not perpendicular to w."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 6, "sentence": "Even if we constrain ||w ||_2 = 1"}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 7, "sentence": ", then also  \\nabla L(w)  is not perpendicular to w."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 8, "sentence": "Am I missing something?"}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 9, "sentence": "What is G_t in Theorem 2.5. It should be defined in the theorem itself."}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 10, "sentence": "There is another symbol G_g which is a constant."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Clarification", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 9, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rylog8i62m", "sid": 10, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Quote", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 0, "sentence": "Thanks for your positive feedback."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 1, "sentence": "(1)."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Lemma 2.4, Point 1: The gradient in your example is indeed perpendicular to w which can be seen as follows."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 3, "sentence": "w\u2019 * \\nabla L(w) = w\u2019 * (2/w\u2019*w)(Aw - L(w)*w) =  (2/w\u2019*w)(w\u2019Aw - L(w)*(w\u2019*w)) =  (2/w\u2019*w)(w\u2019Aw - w\u2019Aw) = 0."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 4, "sentence": "In case of one variable vector, our proof is to take the derivative of c on both sides of F(w) = F(cw), which is the definition of scale-invariance."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 5, "sentence": "Then the left-hand side becomes 0 and the right-hand side becomes w\u2019 * \\nabla F(cw)"}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 6, "sentence": "by chain rule."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 7, "sentence": "Taking c = 1, we can conclude"}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 8, "sentence": "that w\u2019 * \\nabla F(w)  = 0."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 9, "sentence": "(2)"}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 10, "sentence": "."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 11, "sentence": "Theorem 2.5: Sorry G_t should be G_t^{(i)}. We will correct this typo in the next revision of this paper."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 12, "sentence": "For t = 0, G_t^{(i)} are all initialized to some value."}, {"text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 13, "sentence": "The recursion formula for G_t^{(i)} is shown in equation (9)."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "social", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 3}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "refute-question", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 4}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "refute-question", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 5}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "refute-question", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 6}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "refute-question", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "HkgOWxN0T7", "sid": 7}, {"labels": {"alignments": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], "responsetype": "refut